{n_{0}},X^{k_{1}}}$ the usual symmetries. Composition is depicted graphically as follows: $f$$g$$A$$X^{k}$$X^{n_{0}}$$X^{n_{1}}$$X$$B$$X$$X$$C$ In words, we compose morphisms by wiring the dotted wires together into an and gate, by considering the monoidal product of the dashed wires as the dashed wire of the composition, and by feeding a copy the densely dotted input to both circuits. • The 2-cell compositions and identities are trivial, and defined in the obvious way.
